[normal]Conclusion 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]We believe that the Government
[normal]â€™s proposals to reform judicial review are seriously misconceived and are likely to have grave consequences for access 
[normal]to justice. 
[normal]By 
[normal]narrowing the rules on standing and increasing financial risks for claimants and third party interveners, the reforms will cripple the institution of judicial review as a check on the executive. As a result, many instances of abuse of public
[normal] power will go unnoticed, leaving the ordinary citizen without any legal recourse. 
